    • onSaveReturnBtn

      public void onSaveReturnBtn(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws Exception
      Changes an appointment in the Appointments table of the database based on the appointment selected to modify and the data entered by the user. If any vital fields on the form are left blank, the display text is updated to indicate the information needed and no changes are made until all the vital fields are completed. The dates and times selected by the user are tested against business hours and existing appointments, and if there are problems the display text alerts the user and no changes are made until the issues are resolved. Once the appointment has been modified in the database, this method navigates to the Appointments page.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - Clicking the save button.
      Throws:
      Exception - In case of a sql, input, or output exception.
